file=AI & Agents/proto/operational/commands/proto-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "prototype agent", "test new agent", "spin up an experiment", "scaffold", "cage check" \| agent-prototype-kit \| /proto \| · tb=\| "success criteria", "define the eval", "what does success mean", "baseline" \| eval-first-design \| /criteria \| · tb=\| "verdict", "expiry", "promote", "archive", "extend the prototype" \| promote-or-archive-verdict \| /verdict \| · tb=\| "quick prototype", "what fidelity", "paper prototype", "timebox", "scope creep" \| rapid-prototyping-method \| /fidelity \| · p:Precedence=1. An expired prototype outranks everything (verdict before new scaffolds).\n2. Criteria (eval-first-design) before any build question — /proto without frozen criteria bounces to /criteria.\n3. "Extend" routes to promote-or-archive-verdict (extension is its Rail 3 exception, once), never quietly to the kit.\n